  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Pain treatment after periacetabular osteotomy is traditionally based on systemic opioids wich
      have side effects. The purpose of this study is to evaluate the analgetic effect of wound
      infiltration with local anaesthesia after periacetabular osteotomy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
